<h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">Apply for an early-career payment</h1>
<p class="govuk-body">
  The early-career payment service is exclusively for teachers in state-funded
  schools who are qualified in, and currently teaching either:
</p>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li><span class="govuk-body">chemistry</span></li>
  <li><span class="govuk-body">mathematics</span></li>
  <li><span class="govuk-body">foreign languages</span></li>
  <li><span class="govuk-body">physics</span></li>
</ul>

<p class="govuk-body">
  This service will tell you if you are eligible now. Those eligible now will be able to apply for
  their final payment.
</p>

<p class="govuk-body">
  If you want to know more about the qualifying criteria,
  <%= link_to "check our eligibility page", "#{EarlyCareerPayments.eligibility_page_url}", class: "govuk-link" %>.
</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Who is eligible now?</h2>
<p class="govuk-body">
  Mathematics teachers who completed an undergraduate initial teacher training (ITT) or
  started a postgraduate ITT in the 2019 to 2020 academic year can apply for their final
  payment until 31 January 2025.
</p>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Mathematics, physics, chemistry or foreign languages teachers who completed an undergraduate initial teacher training (ITT) or started a postgraduate ITT in the 2020 to 2021 academic year can apply for
  their final payment until 31 January 2025.
</p>

<div class="govuk-inset-text">
  This is the final year eligible teachers can apply for an early-career payment
</div>

<%= link_to new_claim_url(EarlyCareerPayments.routing_name), role: :button, draggable: false, class: "govuk-button govuk-button--start", data: { module: "govuk-button"} do %>
  Start Now
  <%= render partial: "shared/svg_for_govuk_button_start_icon" %>
<% end %>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l">More information</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Email <%= mail_to "earlycareerteacherpayments@digital.education.gov.uk", "earlycareerteacherpayments@digital.education.gov.uk", class: "govuk-link" %> for more information.
</p>
<p class="govuk-body">
  Published 28 January 2020 Last updated 28th October 2020
</p>
